Here's someone who's just fixing my kitchen floor. And I'm pretending right now that I still have a job and am working from home, while I'm sitting on Too Hot to Handle.
If only I could damn it open the file. (Damn One Drive.)
*Voice of a hacker* I'm in.
And that's exactly when he starts drilling super loudly. Yay.
It feels uncomfortably passive-aggressive to turn my air purifier all the way up, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would even be completely okay if he weren't a mask opponent. And do I really need to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't until he's gone.
At least I've finally finished revising Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damn terrifying. Oh yes, this is the good stuff!
I'm doing search and replace for … ➡️ ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I'm sticking with it. Natural language is usually choppy, especially when one gets emotional.
The handyman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he's about to finish.
He went out to cut something (it sounds like that, at least). I secretly checked how far he is. There's still a lot to do :(
Still 7 pages in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's quite neat – mostly changes to the font and very small corrections in direct speech, and I need to make everything a bit more concise. But I really could use a break and a tea right now, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
He just started vacuuming again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me he had prepared a cost estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were stingy and only paid for the part next to the door that is no longer in order. It feels just as good.
The house is being ventilated and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I'm drinking tea in the garden!
